# Archive retention -- installed to /etc/goes-monitor/retention.env (root:root 0600).
# RUNS ON THE ARCHIVE HOST (media-center), not the Pi. Deletes products under
# RETENTION_ROOT older than RETENTION_DAYS, then sweeps the emptied dirs. This is
# what stops the archive growing without bound (goes-sync only ever adds to it).
#
# NOTE: systemd EnvironmentFile does NOT support inline (# ...) comments on a
# value line -- keep values bare, put notes on their own comment lines.
#
# RETENTION_ROOT: the archive dir goes-sync writes into -- i.e. the same path as
# the Pi's sync.env ARCHIVE_DEST. The script is ALSO hard-pinned to /NAS/goes19
# (PIN in goes-retention.sh) as a safety backstop; if the archive ever moves,
# change it in three places: here, PIN, and the unit's RequiresMountsFor.
RETENTION_ROOT=/NAS/goes19
RETENTION_DAYS=7
# Set to 1 to make the timer report-only (logs what it would delete, deletes
# nothing) -- handy for the first run. Back to 0 to actually prune.
DRY_RUN=0
